detailed_optimizations.code_changes:
Option A (layout change): allocate B as Bcol[N][M] (or a 1D array with index j*M+i) so that Bcol[j][k] is contiguous when k varies. Then rewrite kernel:

for (int j=0;j<n;j++) {
  for (int i=0;i<m;i++) {
    DATA_TYPE sum = Bcol[j][i];
    for (int k=i+1;k<m;k++) sum += A[k][i]*Bcol[j][k];
    Bcol[j][i] = alpha*sum;
  }
}

Option B (packing): for each j-block, pack B[k][j..j+JB) into a contiguous buffer Bpack[k][jb] to make k-inner accesses unit-stride; compute and scatter back.

Also add restrict and alignment hints:
void kernel_trmm(..., DATA_TYPE (*restrict A)[M], DATA_TYPE (*restrict B)[N]) and use __builtin_assume_aligned / polybench alignment macros.

Keep original storage but block j so that B[k][j..j+JB) is contiguous and vectorizable:

for (int i=0;i<m;i++) {
  for (int jb=0;jb<n;jb+=JB) {
    int jend = (jb+JB<n)? jb+JB : n;
    // scale existing B[i][j]
    #pragma omp simd
    for (int j=jb;j<jend;j++) B[i][j] *= alpha;
    for (int k=i+1;k<m;k++) {
      DATA_TYPE aik = A[k][i];
      #pragma omp simd
      for (int j=jb;j<jend;j++) {
        B[i][j] += alpha * aik * B[k][j];
      }
    }
  }
}

Notes: move alpha inside accumulation to avoid a final multiply and to keep one pass over B[i][j]. Choose JB as 32/64/128 elements (fit L1/L2 and SIMD width). Add -O3 -ffast-math (if allowed) and ensure DATA_TYPE is float/double accordingly.

Use OpenMP:

#pragma omp parallel for schedule(static)
for (int j=0;j<n;j++) {
  for (int i=0;i<m;i++) {
    DATA_TYPE sum = B[i][j];
    for (int k=i+1;k<m;k++) sum += A[k][i]*B[k][j];
    B[i][j] = alpha*sum;
  }
}

If also doing j-blocking, parallelize over jb blocks. This is race-free because each thread owns distinct j (or jb..jb+JB) columns; reads of B[k][j] are read-only w.r.t. that column’s computation order.

Precompute AT[i][k] = A[k][i] (only for k>i) once:

for (int i=0;i<m;i++)
  for (int k=i+1;k<m;k++) AT[i][k] = A[k][i];

Then inner loop uses AT[i][k] with k varying (unit-stride if AT is row-major and indexed AT[i][k]). Combine with j-blocking.

Memory overhead: ~M*(M-1)/2 elements (or full MxM if simpler).
